You can start with Cargo.toml and src/main.rs. For example:
```rust
fn main() {
    // Your entry point here
}
```
This shows where execution begins.

Great! Start at the entry point in main.rs, then trace to lib.rs where the logic lives. Example:
```rust
use crate::my_module;
fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    my_module::process_json(&args)?;
}
```
Now you can read incrementally and build a mental map.
